SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INCOME UNRELATED TO THE ASSOCIATION'S EXEMPT PURPOSE IS SUBJECT TO FEDERAL INCOME TAXES. INCOME FROM ADVERTISING SALES IS SUBJECT TO TAXATION AS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME (UBI). CORRESPONDING EXPENSES FOR WAGES, PRINTING, DESIGNING, AND DISTRIBUTING THE PUBLICATIONS RELATED TO THE ADVERTISING UBI REDUCED TAXABLE INCOME TO A LEVEL WHERE NO TAX WAS DUE. THE ASSOCIATION HAS ADOPTED ACCOUNTING GUIDANCE FOR RECOGNIZING AND MEASURING UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS. THE ASSOCIATION FOLLOWS STATUTORY REQUIREMENTS FOR INCOME TAX ACCOUNTING AND GENERALLY AVOIDS RISKS ASSOCIATED WITH POTENTIALLY PROBLEMATIC TAX POSITIONS THAT MAY BE CHALLENGED UPON EXAMINATION. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES ANY LIABILITY RESULTING FROM TAXING AUTHORITIES IMPOSING INCOME TAXES FROM ACTIVITIES DEEMED TO BE UNRELATED TO THE ASSOCIATION'S TAX-EXEMPT STATUS WOULD NOT BE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ASSOCIATION'S FEDERAL EXEMPT ORGANIZATION RETURNS ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE, GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AFTER THEY ARE FILED. WITH FEW EXCEPTIONS, THE ASSOCIATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO SUCH EXAMINATIONS FOR TAX YEARS BEFORE 2014.
A DRAFT COPY OF THE TAX RETURN IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO FILING.
FORMAL MONITORING AND ENFORCEMENT IS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD.
COMPENSATION FOR THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR IS BASED ON COMPARABLE POSITIONS IN EDUCATION AND NOT-FOR-PROFIT MANAGEMENT POSITIONS.

ORGANIZATION DOCUMENTS, OTHER THAN PERSONNEL MATTERS, ARE CONSIDERED PUBLIC INFORMATION AND AVAILABLE FOR INSPECTION. HIGHLIGHTS OF BOARD ACTION ARE PUBLISHED ON THE WEB AND IN PRINTED NEWSLETTERS AND MAGAZINES.
